The paper discusses Fog computing, which is a paradigm for managing a highly distributed and possibly virtualized environment that provides compute and network services between sensors and cloud data centers. This topic falls under several computer science sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
